<item>
            <title>[SOLR-12553] SignificantTermsQParserPlugin ignores local params</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12553</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;SignificantTermsQParserPlugin&lt;/em&gt; can take a number of parameters (field, numTerms, minTermLength, etc). However, only &lt;em&gt;field&lt;/em&gt; parameter can be local or global. The rest of parameters can only be global, which does not make sense. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is to use &lt;em&gt;getParam()&lt;/em&gt; method consistently when getting the parameters.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
